  "time_ut": 1656912818,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 19\u0d9a \u0dbb\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0d82 \u0d9a\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "19 crore gold is caught with a katun",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Last night (03) a group of airport customs officers have succeeded in arresting three persons who were trying to illegally leave Katunayake airport worth 19 crore rupees worth of jewellery, gold biscuits and foreign currency.",
        "Jewelery weighing eight and a half kilograms and gold biscuits cut into two, as well as foreign currency worth US$75,000 and \u20ac18,000, were hidden by the three in their luggage and in the pockets of the trousers and shirts they were wearing, in specially prepared fake soles. said an airport customs official.",
        "The airport customs officers have discovered that the two arrested Indian nationals, aged 53 and 42, are professionally involved in smuggling gold and foreign currency through the airports of the two countries.",
        "The airport customs also said that the 46-year-old Sri Lankan who was arrested is a frequent flyer and engaged in business activities.",
        "Jewellery, gold biscuits and foreign currency brought to Katunayake Airport in bulk from India and Dubai are divided into smaller portions and handed over to businessmen and smugglers who are staying at the airport's migrant terminal. The airport customs officers have found out that they have tried to leave.",
        "Accordingly, this consignment of jewellery, gold biscuits and foreign currency was brought to Katunayake Airport by the Sri Lankan flight which arrived from Dubai last night (03) and the Indian Airlines flight AI 273 which arrived from New Delhi at 01.40 in the morning today (04). It has been found in the preliminary investigations carried out by the customs officers that it has been brought to",
        "The formal customs investigation was conducted by the Deputy Director of Customs Mr. UTB Alavathugoda, where he ordered the confiscation of all these jewellery, gold biscuits and foreign currency, and also ordered these three persons to pay a fine of 25,000 rupees each and 75,000 rupees. have done"
      ],
